channel.description: it says i have an error when i try to log in to a server, what do i do?

item.title: Error-help
item.dc:creator: @xCrackingx xCrackingx
item.description:
@xCrackingx wrote:

Yes, you do need to be on the network, EX if you wanted to join Haxx0r3lit3scape and it required hamachi, you would need to join it’s hamachi network. Let’s say the network is haxx0rscape. Click join new server, should be down in the bottom RIGHT corner. then select join existing server, and type in haxx0rscape. It will also require a password, let’s say the password is 1234. For the password, type that in and you’re connected to the network. Now all you have to do is put in the ip ex:5.152.535.345, type that in the IP area and log in.

item.title: Error-help
item.dc:creator: @xCrackingx xCrackingx
item.description:
@xCrackingx wrote:

When you try to log into a server, and it gives you an error, chances are it’s down or needs Hamachi. USUALLY, Ip addresses like 5.146.234.244 will need Hamachi, but not always. If the server is down, it will tell you that you have an error. Just keep trying different servers.

ALSO, this is in the wrong section, use MoparScape questions for these types of things.
